 Need 1 more week of data.\n\n**My thinking:** OBI magnitude is emerging as the single best predictor we have. Strong negative OBI (bearish OB) + contrarian YES = 83% WR is remarkable. V5b OBI sizing (full at OBI\u2705, half at OBI\u274c) is the right framework, but we might want to consider an OBI GATE instead: BLOCK trades when OBI > +0.5 (strong bullish = 0% WR). This is only 2 trades so far \u2014 need n\u226510 to validate. Track aggressively.\n\n**Decision:** \n1. Add OBI>0.5 gate to V5b spec as OPTIONAL upgrade (activate when n\u226510 OBI>0.5 trades)\n2. Track 20h removal for V6 (need W14 full week data)\n3. Order book aggregation: use top-20 $1-level depth for consistent OBI readings\n\n**Next:** P2 \u2014 Smart entry parameter review with Apr 1 evening failures.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-02 06:17 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] BTC -2.8% Overnight Drop: Regime & Alpha Analysis for Apr 2\n\n**Task:** P4 alpha research \u2014 analyze BTC selloff, regime projection, funding/liquidation signals for today's session\n\n**Finding \u2014 Overnight Selloff:**\n- BTC: $69,310 \u2192 $66,217 low (-4.5%), now $66,775. 24h vol $1.4B.\n- Sharp dump 00-04h UTC (Asia session). Consolidating $66.2-66.8K",
